Observations
The codebase has a well-structured multi-agent system with BaseAgent, LLMGateway, ModelRouter, ToolRouter, and PageIndexClient all implemented. The critical issues are:

MarketResearcherAgent.run() calls self.llm.generate() directly (line 85) instead of self.generate_with_tools() — bypassing all tool invocation. FinancialAnalystAgent correctly uses generate_with_tools().
LLMGateway is fully implemented but never called — BaseAgent.generate_with_tools() calls model_router.get_client_for_agent() directly, bypassing the gateway's rate limiting, backoff, caching, and fallback chain.
FetchFinancialStatementsTool.execute() is defined as a sync method (line 149) while BaseTool.execute() is async — causing silent failures when awaited.
DealState has no buyer_thesis, deal_stage, or deal_goal fields; system prompts are generic.
PageIndexClient.query() passes deal_id correctly via filters dict, but BaseAgent.retrieve_context() (line 233) calls self.memory.query(query, top_k=top_k) without passing filters — so deal_id is never used as a metadata filter.
MCPClient.query() sends JSON-RPC to {base_url}/mcp — an endpoint that Finnhub, FMP, etc. don't expose. The direct REST tool clients (FinnhubTool, AlphaVantageTool, etc.) work correctly and are already registered in ToolRouter.
Approach
Fix each root cause in dependency order: async/sync mismatch first (it's a silent crash), then wire LLMGateway into generate_with_tools(), then fix the MarketResearcherAgent tool bypass, then fix RAG query construction, then enrich system prompts with deal-goal injection, and finally deprecate the broken MCP JSON-RPC path in favor of the working direct REST tools.

